I can reproduce this bug on mitaka by following the above instructions:

For example, if your total quotas of instances is 10, and 8/10 used, you can do this:
mysql;
use nova;
UPDATE `quota_usages` SET `reserved`=2 WHERE `project_id`='827fb1414de740569efd53580bafc2f0' and `resource`='instances' LIMIT 1;
Then, refresh your dashboard in the web browser, you will get this bug.


My conclusion( same as Eugene Wang reported): 

1. This bug has nothing to do with Nova.
2. and dashboard(web->project->compute->overview perspectivedoes) shows the WRONG limits of resources which should include the count of the reserved resources.
